cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses the use of blockchains for storing metadata and improving privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also analyzes the evolution of metadata utilization in recent years, which involves data management (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential criminal use of blockchain, which relates to cybercrime (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of developing countermeasures.
